Create github.com/outdoorsea/herald-private as a separate Go module that
extracts bridge tool wrappers (comms, health) into private extensions.
The module registers two extensions via init() using extensions.Register().

To support external module access, create public packages:
- tools/ — Tool and Executor interfaces (type-aliased in internal/tools)
- extensions/ — extension registry with factory pattern (cfg any)

The internal/extensions package becomes a thin wrapper around the public
registry. The herald-private module reads bridge URLs from env vars
(HERALD_BRIDGE_COMMS_URL, HERALD_BRIDGE_HEALTH_URL) via a local
BridgesConfig struct. Includes go.mod with replace directive pointing
to local herald checkout.

